@title Chain Estate Presale
 @dev Contract responsible for the Chain Estate presale mechanism

@dev Once the CHES token contract is deployed, this function is used to set a reference to that token in this contract.
 @param CHESTokenAddress address of the ChainEstate token.

@dev Gets the amount of CHES the sender owns.
 @return the CHES balance of the sender

@dev Returns the contract address
 @return contract address

@dev Returns the CHES token address
 @return CHES token contract address

typeDescriptions.typeString: literal_string "You cannot purchase this many CHES tokens, that would put you past your presale cap."

arguments.value: You cannot purchase this many CHES tokens, that would put you past your presale cap.

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "You cannot purchase this many CHES tokens, that would put you past your presale cap."

documentation.text: @dev Allows a user to pay BNB for CHES tokens. Conversion rate is 1 BNB to BNBToCHESRate CHES where BNBToCHESRate is the variable defined in the contract.

@dev Only owner function to change the presale CHES token purchase cap per user.
 @param newPurchaseCap the new CHES token purchase cap in CHES (NOT BNB). Use the conversion rate to figure out how many CHES to set here.

@dev Only owner function to change the conversion rate for BNB to CHES.
 @param newConversionRate the new BNB to CHES conversion rate.

@dev Only owner function to withdraw the BNB from this contract.
 @param amount the amount of BNB to withdraw from the pre-sale contract.

@dev Gets the amount of BNB that the contract has.
 @return the amount of BNB the contract has.

@dev Gets the CHES token balance of the contract.
 @return the amount of CHES tokens the contract has.

natspec.details: Contract responsible for the Chain Estate presale mechanism

changeBNBToCHESRate(uint256).details: Only owner function to change the conversion rate for BNB to CHES.

params.newConversionRate: the new BNB to CHES conversion rate.

changeCHESPurchaseCap(uint256).details: Only owner function to change the presale CHES token purchase cap per user.

params.newPurchaseCap: the new CHES token purchase cap in CHES (NOT BNB). Use the conversion rate to figure out how many CHES to set here.

getContractBNB().details: Gets the amount of BNB that the contract has.

returns._0: the amount of BNB the contract has.

getContractTokens().details: Gets the CHES token balance of the contract.

returns._0: the amount of CHES tokens the contract has.

getUserBalance().details: Gets the amount of CHES the sender owns.

returns._0: the CHES balance of the sender

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

purchaseCHESTokens().details: Allows a user to pay BNB for CHES tokens. Conversion rate is 1 BNB to BNBToCHESRate CHES where BNBToCHESRate is the variable defined in the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setToken(address).details: Once the CHES token contract is deployed, this function is used to set a reference to that token in this contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawBNB(uint256).details: Only owner function to withdraw the BNB from this contract.

params.amount: the amount of BNB to withdraw from the pre-sale contract.
